Refuse too large map data size

Map https://test.touch-mapper.org/fi/map?map=B57bd2c8b2f3d765 says:
Major road Turunväylä, 8590 meters
From the center to the west part
Crosses east edge in the south and west edge near the center
But that's impossible, both by visual inspection, and because parts of the roads must exist near east edge or south-east corner since the road crosses east edge.

---

If the osm file is over 25M before pruning in normal or no-buildings mode, or after pruning in big-roads-only mode, refuse the operation as following. Instead of monitoring existence of the stl file by polling head requests, browser will poll GET for the meta.json (S3 /map/info/<id>.json). That file is added key 

--

In road size classification, use fewer elements so that pieces of roads don't get cut off. OR: group roads by name, not by osmId, and assign highest score of any osmId segment of the road. Road names can maybe be hashed into integers for memory savings -- a rare hash conflict is acceptable.

Shouldn't road ranking code been removed from process-request.py?

Only count road meters within bounding box

